ICO Rule 2: If they don't sell out I the first 3 days, you're in trouble.

Every one of my threads are very simple ideas. I find the simplest explanations and tips to be most effective.
19/ So pack your bags. Alt season is about to commence.pic.twitter.com/EaeGxX6GZN
18/ Long thread short: I'm looking to start building into alt positions this week + next 2 Incremental buys > getting increasingly larger
17/ Tough part here is not getting greedy with alt gains. Wait too long and $ BTC starts to correct (weaken) significantly, bring alts down 2
16/ And swing back into long $ BTC, selling expensive alts to buy $ BTC when it becomes cheap again.
15/ Think of the ideal short/long exposure like a pendulum. The long exposure should shift to alts as $ BTC is done with it's strong run
14/ This seems simple, yet traders (I've been guilty before) still sell weaker alts to strong $ BTC or buy stronger alts with weak $ BTC
13/ Similarly you would scale out of stronger alts when expensive > into weaker $ BTC (cheaper) getting more bang for your Alt-coin
12/ Rather than try to time this exactly at top or bottom (impossible), it makes sense to scale into alts as $ BTC gets relatively expensive
11/ ...when $ BTC is strongest (expensive) and buy alts when they are weakest (cheapest). You are getting most bang for your $ BTC
10/ As $ BTC approaches top of channel and has higher chance of reaching resistance, you have opportunity to exchange your $ BTC for alts...
9/ Another way to think of this is the alts are becoming weaker (cheaper) in terms of $ BTC. You could buy 100 $ LTC yesterday -> 120 today
8/ Each day $ BTC gets stronger (more expensive), it can buy more alts than previous day. $5100 worth of alt yesterday -> $5500 worth today
7/ Since almost all alts are priced in $ BTC, you see their price drop as $ BTC rises to top of channel. $ BTC becomes stronger (expensive)
6/ To keep things simple assume your portfolio is only composed of $ BTC and alts. I also use long/short interchangeably for buy/sell
5/ 'Timing' the market based on relative valuation and coin positioning (long or short) combine to form my approach for alt season
